# Memory context (MemForge)

The following is the contents of the operator's MEMORY.md index. Treat it as session-start context: identity, accumulated feedback, ongoing project state, and references to external systems.

When the operator references a memory by title (e.g., "the AWS infra rollup"), follow the link in MEMORY.md to read the underlying file before answering.

When the operator asks you to remember something cross-session, write it to a new file in the memory folder using the v0.3.0 frontmatter schema (see `~/claude-projects/memforge/spec/SPEC.md`). The filesystem watcher will commit the file automatically.

## MEMORY.md content

@~/.claude/projects/PER_CWD_WORKSPACE_NAME/memory/MEMORY.md

@~/.claude/global-memory/MEMORY.md

